<!-- ============ MODAL: STORY 4 â€” EQUITY INVESTIGATION ============ -->
<div class="overlay" id="modal-story-4">
  <div class="modal">
    <button class="modal-close" onclick="closeModal()">Ã—</button>
    <div class="modal-head">
      <div class="modal-rank-pill" style="background: var(--ink); color: var(--accent-2);">Equity Investigation Â· Foundational Â· 14 May 2026</div>
      <div class="modal-uni-name">The prevalence-disposal gap.</div>
      <div class="modal-uni-sub">Students report nine times more discriminatory incidents than reach formal complaint at the IITs we surveyed. The gap is the most actionable equity signal we measure â€” it indicates students do not feel safe filing.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="modal-body">

      <div class="modal-section">
        <h4>The method <span class="h4-source">Pipelines 2 and 3 in deliberate tension</span></h4>
        <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.6;color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:12px;">
          Sub-metric 5.3 in our methodology uses two independent data sources: anonymous survey data (Pipeline 3) on whether students have experienced discriminatory incidents in the past 12 months, and RTI responses (Pipeline 2) on formal complaints filed and disposed during the same window. The ratio of survey-reported prevalence to formal-complaint counts is itself the signal.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.6;color:var(--ink);">
          A small gap (e.g. ratio &lt;3) suggests students who experience discrimination feel safe enough to file. A large gap (ratio &gt;10) suggests they do not. The average across the 14 IITs we have full data for: <strong>9.2 to 1</strong>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="modal-section">
        <h4>The IIT-by-IIT breakdown <span class="h4-source">Highest-gap institutions</span></h4>
        <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:13px;">
